==Statistics==

GitHub was launched in February 2008<ref>[http://github.com/blog/1-hotkeys-and-wikis First GitHub blog post]</ref>.

In a talk at [[Yahoo!]] on 2-24-2009, GitHub team members announced that during the year that GitHub had been online, it accumulated 46,000 public repositories, of which 17,000 in the last month alone. 6,200 repositories have been forked at least once and 4,600 have merged from fork. In another talk delivered at Yahoo! on 2009-07-27, Tom Preston-Werner announced that the numbers have risen to 90,000 unique public repositories, of which 10,000 in the last month; 12,000 have been forked at least once, for a total of 135,000 repositories<ref>[http://wiki.dandascalescu.com/essays/pita-threshold The PITA Threshold - GitHub vs. CPAN]</ref>.

